data.description: Step into this charming 1920s home on a corner lot, boasting original features. Sunlit sunroom welcomes you with hardwood floors flowing throughout, accompanied by abundant windows. Spacious living room offers a cozy wood-burning fireplace and an extra nook for reading or office space. An adjoining large dining area features an original built-in buffet. Just steps away, the kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances and provides access to the backyard and a 1-car detached garage. Main level includes a bedroom and a full shared bathroom with a tub/shower combo and hexagon tile floors. Upstairs, two large bedrooms await, private balcony access and a three-quarter bathroom. Unfinished lower level holds immense potential, with ample storage space and a washer/dryer. Conveniently located within walking distance to the bus stop and close to Theodore Wirth Regional Park, Bassett Creek, and highway access.
